Class QueryResultWidget

  com.fluidops.iwb.widget.AbstractWidget<QueryResultWidget.Config>

All Implemented Interfaces:
Widget<QueryResultWidget.Config>
public class QueryResultWidget
extends AbstractWidget<QueryResultWidget.Config>

QueryResultWidget to render the results of a query as desired (fully customizable) (see test case 'QueryResults' for more examples) Usage examples a) Without pattern: default {{ #widget: QueryResult | query = 'SELECT ?Name ?FirstName WHERE { pubmed:id/21293379 pubmed:author ?a . ?a pubmed:lastName ?Name . ?a pubmed:foreName ?FirstName . }' }} b) With explicit template {{ #widget: QueryResult | query = 'SELECT ?Name ?FirstName WHERE { pubmed:id/21293379 pubmed:author ?a . ?a pubmed:lastName ?Name . ?a pubmed:foreName ?FirstName . }' | template = '{{{FirstName}}} {{{Name}}}' }} c) With template + format {{ #widget: QueryResult | query = 'SELECT ?Name ?FirstName WHERE { pubmed:id/21293379 pubmed:author ?a . ?a pubmed:lastName ?Name . ?a pubmed:foreName ?FirstName . }' | template = '{{{FirstName}}} {{{Name}}}' | format = 'ul' }} e) With explicit template (numbers) => media wiki {{ #widget: QueryResult | query = 'SELECT ?Name ?FirstName WHERE { pubmed:id/21293379 pubmed:author ?a . ?a pubmed:lastName ?Name . ?a pubmed:foreName ?FirstName . }' | template = '{{{2}}} {{{1}}}' }} f) With value resolver {{#widget: QueryResult | query = 'SELECT ?image ?time WHERE { ?? :image ?image . ?? :time ?time }' | template = '{{{image}}}
{{{time}}}' | valueResolver = 'time=MS_TIMESTAMP2DATE,image=IMAGE' }}
